<TITLE> KAFCO man found dead </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 26 (bdnews24.com)Police on Friday recovered the dead body of a Chittagong Karnaphuli Fertiliser Company official believed to have been killed in the early hours. The body of Aurangajeb Hossain Mithu, 43, a purchase officer, was recovered from a sixth-floor flat at Mim Tower at around 6pm, Banaj Kumar Majumder, deputy commissioner (police) of Chittagong city (north), told bdnews24.com. Police suspect that criminals might have killed him either by pressing pillow onto his face or by hacking him by knives or other sharp weapons. None was present at the house during the recovery of the body. The police officer quoted neighbours as saying that Mithu and his wife had been living separately for around one and a half months. bd
